tip.text: The deep fried salted egg cuttlefish (sotong) was very nice. Love their sambal belacan too. Will definitely go back. I just wish they didn't allow people to smoke inside the cafe.
The Glow worm cave (45 mins) was nice as it included a short boat ride in the dark to see the glow worms. A magical experience. Ruakuri cave is longer (2 hours) but the walk is easy and interesting.
Beautiful scenery to say the least. Learn fun facts about the set and simply enjoy and appreciate the creativity and detailed work that went into creating Hobbiton. Wear comfortable walking shoes.
An interesting experience to see the different craters, pools, and colours. Smelly at times but not all the way. There are 3 routes to choose from - the longest walk taking about 1hr 45 mins.
They have a variety of walks from short to long walks - just follow the colour-coded arrows. Can get muddy if it's been raining so wear appropriate shoes. The treewalk was a nice experience.
Loved the private room facing the lake. You come out feeling like you're walking on air. Only 30 mins per booking so come prepared with your swimsuit on. Towel rentals are $5 plus a $5 deposit.
Learn how the Maori warriors trained, watch Maori traditional games, learn about their crafts and how they prepared their food. And be amazed by their performances. A must see. Dinner was good too.
The Indian and the Thai food are both very tasty. The Thai chicken stir fried with basil, chillies and veges was good. And the tom yum was nice. Not very authentic Thai food but still delicious.

venue.name: Greens Traditional Indian And Thai Quisine

tip.text: The nasi lemak with chicken masak merah was delicious. The chicken was very tasty, the ikan bilis was crispy, the sambal was nice and the rice light but also tasty.
Their twisted tembikai (watermelon) was not too bad. Their candy floss coffee is pretty cool.

tip.text: The beef stew, salad and watermelon lemonade were very tasty.
The OMG sushi was nice but a bit expensive.
The grilled quarter chicken with puréed potato was quite nice. Would have been complete with green vegetables on the side.
Love the salted egg crab here. Very fresh and juicy. Butter prawns were nice and crispy too!
Love the teh tarik peng here.
Love the chili dog here. Burgers are nice too. Homemade patties.

formattedAddress: 136, Jln Layang-Layang, Kpg Malaysia Jaya, (Jalan Astana)

tip.text: Nice spacious apartment-style accommodation with a small kitchen & dining area. Sleeps 6 people comfortably.
Wonderful service even during the busiest time of the year. Nice rooms and amenities. We will definitely be back again.
Nice casual place to relax and bring family or friends. Nice view of the sea. Can go down to the beach or swim in their pool. Only RM5 entrance fee for day trippers. Nice drinks/food at cafe too.
The sushi set (choice of 3 types) was very nice. Friendly staff.
Order your food very early, and avoid staying in room 3 if you can. It's opposite the kitchen. Clean & decent rooms for the price that you pay. Nice staff. Aircons are a bit noisy.
The salmon pepper rice was quite nice. But not for those with a big appetite. I like that they use environment-friendly paper straws instead of plastic straws.
Nice fruit slushes. But very expensive. The Calamansi slush was invigorating and refreshing.
The cucumber apple mint drink is very refreshing. The pink lemonade is not bad. Spaghetti bolognese & pasta pomodoro with salmon are tasty. Free water and free wifi. :)
Nice Indonesian food overall at a reasonable price considering the set up and scenery of the padi fields. Tables are well spread out under private gazebos. I'd definitely go back.
Tom yum here is nice and this is where you can get Malaysian Teh Tarik (frothy milk tea). Tasted a bit different but was still nice. They also have roti canai.
Not the greatest seafood I've had. Actually enjoyed the BBQ corn from the stalls on the beach a lot more. It's a must try. Spicy, salty or sweet or everything. Absolutely delicious. And cheap!
Beautiful scenery. Lots of local shops along the way that require lots of bargaining. Try the BBQ corn. It's delicious. Choose sweet or spicy or both.
Medium size airport. Some typical duty-free shops inside and cafés too. There's a spa too for that last minute massage or manicure.

venue.name: Ngurah Rai International Airport (DPS) (Bandar Udara Internasional Ngurah Rai)

tip.text: The food court at the top floor has an international selection of food stalls to choose from. I like the "open air" setup of the mall. Some nice shops too. Mixture of local & international brands.
Enjoyed my salmon steak and watermelon juice. Their rice with prawns was nice too.
I like their fried fish dishes like siakap masak pedas but it's not cheap. Generally the food is quite nice. Service is usually good and fast unless there's a big crowd.
Wouldn't order the cheese burger again. Was rather dry and so was the roast chicken. A glass of ice water costs RM1. Don't think I'm going back. Only the simple quiet atmosphere was quite nice.
Nice place to hang out. I'm not a coffee drinker but my friends love the coffee here and say it's "better than Starbucks".
I like the Niku Soba (noodles in soup with slices of beef & seaweed). The macha smoothie & mango smoothie are yummy too. Beef steak is ok. Some of their sushi is nice too.
They now have some Indonesian food choices as well as Chinese & local dishes like curry laksa, rojak & yong tau foo. Generally, their food is not bad.

tip.text: Food is cheap & not bad. Good variety of food including vegetables. Good for a quick meal.
Tailoring is good but a bit pricy. Nice people. They sell ready made baju kurung and some material too. Used to be "Barbara J".
Love the minced chicken with hot basil & rice. Tom yam is very tasty but expensive. Good & fast service. Thai iced tea & lemongrass juice are nice too.
Some nice and interesting burger choices. Small cozy place. Interesting graffiti decor.

formattedAddress: Taman Rekreasi Lembah Kiara (Jalan Abang Haji Openg, Taman Tun Dr Ismail)
location.crossStreet: Jalan Abang Haji Openg, Taman Tun Dr Ismail

tip.text: Come around 5pm & stay till nightfall. The place is huge & beautiful. Flower Dome & Cloud Forest were worth the SGD$28. But domes were a bit too dark at night. Skyway was $5. A very relaxing place.
Pretty yummy burgers. Pricy (about RM20-30 for a burger with fries & refillable soft drink) but worth the treat. Young vibrant environment. Service staff are nice. Long queues so expect to wait.
The tom yam is sure to make your mouth buzz. Very tasty. Kangkung belacan was delicious. Green curry ok but heavy on the coconut milk. Mango cheesecake quite nice. Service was good.
